  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is a serious financial crime with a comprehensive legal framework designed to prevent, detect, and prosecute such activities. Here's an overview of the legal framework:\n\n1. International Level\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- United Nations Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Basel Committee on Banking Supervision guidelines\n\n2. United States\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) regulations\n- USA PATRIOT Act\n- Currency and Foreign Transactions Reporting Act\n\n3. Key Legal Requirements\n- Customer due diligence\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Record-keeping obligations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) procedures\n\n4. Criminalization\n- Money laundering is a federal criminal offense\n- Potential penalties include:\n- Substantial fines\n- Imprisonment\n- Asset forfeiture\n\n5. Enforcement Agencies\n- Financial Crimes Enforcement Network (FinCEN)\n- Internal Revenue Service (IRS)\n- Department of Justice\n- Federal Bureau of Investigation\n\n6. Regulatory Compliance\n- Financial institutions must implement robust AML programs\n- Regular reporting and auditing requirements\n- Potential sanctions for non-compliance\n\nThis framework aims to prevent criminal financial activities and protect the financial system's integrity.",
